  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Warehouse Assistant (Up to $3k)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job responsibilities: </strong></p><ul><li>Manage daily warehouse operations, including goods receiving, picking, packing, loading.</li><li>Ensure accurate inventory management through stock counts, reconciliations, and system updates.</li><li>Coordinate and liaise effectively with inter-department related all warehouse and logistic concerns.</li><li>Maintain proper storage and labelling of products in accordance with safety and quality standards.</li><li>Perform inventory control tasks and checks on quantities, quality and availability against records, following established inventory control procedures.</li><li>Monitor and improve space utilization and warehouse layout for operational efficiency.</li><li>Assist on annual stock take and cycle count.</li><li>Ensure warehouse cleanliness, orderliness, and compliance with workplace safety regulations.</li><li>May assigned to drive the company vehicle as and when needed</li><li>All other administrative tasks as assigned by superiors from time to time.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum 2 Years of experience in warehouse roles      </li><li>Must possess at least SG Class 3 license, forklift driving license     </li><li>Shelf-life monitoring for spares     </li><li>Computer literacy     </li><li>Knowledge of warehouse safety protocols and logistics documentation.</li><li>Physically fit</li></ul><p><strong>Working Days / Hours</strong></p><ul><li>5 days work week / 37.5 hours</li></ul><p><strong>Benefits</strong></p><ul><li>Company transport : Admiralty/ Clementi/ Sengkang/ Tampines MRT</li><li>Comprehensive health insurance with hospitalization and specialist coverage, plus dental benefits.</li><li>Professional development and advancement.</li><li>Dynamic and supportive work environment.</li><li>Birthday Reward / Leave</li><li>Meal, Transport and Laundry allowance.</li><li>Long Service Awards / Leave</li><li>Recognition awards.</li><li>AWS</li></ul>",
